#. type: Content of: <guide><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRUB2 migration from GRUB Legacy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The goal of this guide is to provide you with a smooth migration from GRUB\n"
"Legacy to GRUB2.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "What's Grub?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Grub is one of the most commonly found boot loaders in use on non-embedded\n"
"Linux machines. The role of Grub is to facilitate the Linux kernel being loaded\n"
"from your disk into memory and start executing the Linux kernel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "So Why Migrate?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Firstly, GRUB Legacy is no longer maintained and as such no longer receives\n"
"updates. GRUB Legacy was created at a time when the developers felt safe in\n"
"making several assumptions which no longer hold true today. For example,\n"
"GRUB Legacy is unable to boot from disks larger than 2TB and assumes that\n"
"newer filesystems wouldn't come to replace <path>/boot</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:51
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"GRUB2 aims to be more robust, more portable, more powerful and is maintained\n"
"with a cleaner code base. GRUB2 supports more hardware configurations, more\n"
"filesystems and more drive layouts than its predecessor.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migration to GRUB2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Migration to GRUB2 is fairly straightforward: it will be pulled in as part\n"
"of your regular upgrade process by your package manager. If it is not pulled\n"
"in automatically, you can always install <c>sys-boot/grub:2</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Boot Drive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:78
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The first important part is to understand what your bootable drive is. For\n"
"many people it will be <path>/dev/sda</path>. The easiest way to find this is\n"
"to look at how your existing GRUB Legacy is setup by viewing\n"
"<path>/boot/grub/grub.conf</path>. An example one is provided below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You must have your <path>/boot</path> mounted to be able to view these files.\n"
"It should be as simple as <c>mount /boot</c> to mount <path>/boot</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:89 en/grub2-migration.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "/boot/grub/grub.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"default 0\n"
"timeout 30\n"
"splashimage=(hd0,0)/boot/grub/splash.xpm.gz\n"
"\n"
"title Gentoo Linux 3.2.12\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /boot/kernel-3.2.12-gentoo root=/dev/sda3 quiet dolvm\n"
"initrd /boot/initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-3.2.12-gentoo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Based on the above file we know that <c>(hd0)</c> is the boot drive but we\n"
"must map this to a real device. To know this you must view\n"
"<path>/boot/grub/device.map</path>. An example one is provided below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "/boot/grub/device.map"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:107
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(fd0) /dev/fd0\n"
"(hd0) /dev/sda\n"
"(hd1) /dev/sdb\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "Based on the above file we know that <path>/dev/sda</path> is the boot drive.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing and Configuring GRUB2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:123
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The next step is to install and configure GRUB2 on your <path>/boot</path>\n"
"partition without removing GRUB Legacy from your MBR. The example below\n"
"uses <path>/dev/sda</path> but you must replace it with your boot drive path.\n"
"The first step installs the necessary GRUB2 files to <path>/boot/grub2</path>,\n"
"while the second step scans your available kernels and generates a suitable\n"
"config file to <path>/boot/grub2/grub.cfg</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing and configuring GRUB2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:132
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>grub2-install --grub-setup=/bin/true /dev/sda</i>\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.\n"
"# <i>grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg</i>\n"
"Generating grub.cfg ...\n"
"Found linux image: /boot/kernel-3.2.12-gentoo\n"
"Found initrd image: /boot/initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-3.2.12-gentoo\n"
"done\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:142
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>grub2-mkconfig</c> has strict naming requirements for kernels and initramfs images. A\n"
"kernel must be named <c>kernel-${version}</c> or <c>vmlinuz-${version}</c>\n"
"while an initramfs must be named <c>initramfs-${version}.img</c>,\n"
"<c>initramfs-genkernel-${version}</c>,\n"
"<c>initramfs-genkernel-${arch}-${version}</c>,\n"
"<c>initrd-${version}.img</c>, <c>initrd.img-${version}</c>,\n"
"<c>initrd-${version}.gz</c>, or <c>initrd-${version}</c>.\n"
"Together with ${version}, the filename must match a corresponding kernel\n"
"that is available in <path>/boot</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "Chainloading GRUB2 from GRUB Legacy to test the setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Because a broken GRUB configuration could mean an unbootable\n"
"system, we want to test our GRUB2 configuration before making it permanent.\n"
"To do this we will chainload GRUB2 from GRUB Legacy. This is done by adding\n"
"a new section into <path>/boot/grub/grub.conf</path>. An example is shown\n"
"below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Be aware that your root may be different from <c>(hd0,0)</c> used in the\n"
"example, and make sure you reuse the same root value from your\n"
"<path>/boot/grub/grub.conf</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:174
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"default 0\n"
"timeout 30\n"
"splashimage=(hd0,0)/boot/grub/splash.xpm.gz\n"
"\n"
"<i>title GRUB2 Chainload\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /boot/grub2/i386-pc/core.img\n"
"boot</i>\n"
"\n"
"title Gentoo Linux 3.2.12\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /boot/kernel-3.2.12-gentoo root=/dev/sda3 quiet dolvm\n"
"initrd /boot/initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-3.2.12-gentoo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At this point you should reboot your machine and select <c>GRUB2 Chainload</c>\n"
"from the GRUB menu when your machine begins to boot.  You will be presented with\n"
"another GRUB menu which should advertise itself as GRUB 2.0.0 or higher at the\n"
"top and show your available kernel(s) to boot.  Should this not work, simply\n"
"reboot your system and pick your normal boot option instead of <c>GRUB2\n"
"Chainload</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "Replacing and removing GRUB Legacy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:205
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At this point, if everything worked successfully, you can replace GRUB Legacy\n"
"and remove it from your system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:210
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Since you've rebooted your system, you may need to mount <path>/boot</path>\n"
"again. Make sure to use your own boot drive path instead of\n"
"<path>/dev/sda</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "Replacing GRUB Legacy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:216
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>grub2-install /dev/sda</i>\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.\n"
"# <i>rm -rf /boot/grub/</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:222
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"At this point you can use your package manager to remove <c>sys-boot/grub:0</c>.\n"
"The migration is complete.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:231
#, no-wrap
msgid "Maintaining GRUB2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:236
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Whenever you install a new kernel, you must perform the next step so\n"
"that your GRUB2 configuration recognizes the new kernel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:241
#, no-wrap
msgid "You must have your <path>/boot</path> partition mounted for this step.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:244
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing a new kernel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/grub2-migration.xml:245
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg</i>\n"
"Generating grub.cfg ...\n"
"Found linux image: /boot/kernel-3.3.8-gentoo\n"
"Found initrd image: /boot/initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-3.3.8-gentoo\n"
"Found linux image: /boot/kernel-3.2.12-gentoo\n"
"Found initrd image: /boot/initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-3.2.12-gentoo\n"
"done\n"
msgstr ""

